info.name: Google Darkest Fusion 2/2
info.description: Do you like my style? Please support my work and fund me a coffee (via PayPal to the left of "Install" button). Also share style with your friends. Thank you for being awesome! Darkest Fusion supports almost every Google site. Due to an style size limit Darkest Fusion has been divided into 2 parts. That part contains dark theme for less used Google sites: Developers, Firebase, Docs, Forms, Flights, Play, Music, Scholar and Script. First style is available >>> there <<< Keep and Support currently have stock dark themes. Originally based on great work by DeathTBO who abandoned his project so I decided to continue his work by rebuilting everything from scratch. I hope you like my vision for Dark Google :)
info.additionalInfo: If you find issue, describe it accurate please. Provide screen, tell me language/area and browser you are using because often it depends of them. See example. Please don't give thumbs down/OK in comments with small issues. I will fix them as soon as possible. Thank you. Known issues: - you tell me. Additional informations: - on Chrome/Opera Homepage may not work correctly, solution there - In Docs, I can't make exceptions for colorized tables and I can't make 100% dark Sheets because websites code overwrites it Changelog: * 1.31 - 08.02.2021 - fixes to Travel, * 1.3 - 29.12.2020 - HUGE amount of fixes related to Travel and Flights, * 1.2 - 20.12.2020 - again I reached limits on main style 1/2 so moved redesigned Shopping here https://i.imgur.com/AfEuBng.png :( * 1.11 - 18.12.2020 - fixes to Developers and Script (thx @Marobon), * 1.10 - 24.11.2020 - fixes to Docs, Forms, * 1.09 - 08.06.2020 - fixes to Docs-Drive, * 1.08 - 08.06.2020 - fixes to Docs, * 1.07 - 16.07.2020 - fixes to Developers and to Firebase (thx @kldjflkasjdfasdf for info) * 1.06 - 07.05.2020 - fixes to Play, * 1.05 - 11.04.2020 - fixes to Music and Play, * 1.04 - 31.03.2020 - fixes to Forms, * 1.03 - 14.03.2020 - fixed some bugs on Docs (thanks @Nhiet and @Digdown50 for info) * 1.02 - 26.02.2020 - more fixes to Music (again thanks @EriolAncalagon for help), * 1.01 - 24.02.2020 - fixes to Music (thanks @EriolAncalagon for info), * 1.0 - 21.02.2020 - style had been divided into two parts due to a style limit size (and userstyles.org admins doesn't give a f**k on that site - I can't contact with them), first style is available there, also fixes to Docs and Firebase (thx @Kebab Boy, @ngranger.tech and @Idomo for help),
